You are working on a Shopify OS 2.0 theme based on Horizon, customized with OPTICA (homepage) and Atelier (components).

## 🔒 Core Rules

- DO NOT modify Horizon core files unless explicitly asked:
  - assets/base.css
  - sections/header.liquid
  - core JS utilities

- Prefer editing:
  - assets/atelier-luxury.css (homepage styles only)
  - assets/optica-pdp.css (product page styles only)
  - templates/*.json (layout + structure)
  - sections/optica-* (custom sections)
  - sections/atelier-* (reusable components)

---

## 🎯 Styling Rules

- Homepage styles MUST be scoped under:
  body.template-index

- Product page styles MUST be scoped under:
  body.template-product

- Do NOT add global styles without scoping.

- Reuse existing gold luxury design system:
  - borders
  - spacing
  - typography
  - button styles

---

## 🧱 Section Rules

- Sections are controlled via:
  templates/index.json
  templates/product.json

- NEVER hardcode section order in Liquid.
- ALWAYS modify JSON templates for layout changes.

---

## 🧩 Blocks (Product Page)

- Product blocks are registered in:
  blocks/_product-details.liquid

- When adding features:
  - Prefer creating a new block instead of modifying existing ones
  - Keep compatibility with Shopify dynamic sources

---

## ⚠️ Safety Rules

- Do NOT:
  - Break schema structure
  - Rename JSON keys (Shopify is strict)
  - Remove existing settings used in Theme Editor
  - Hardcode content that should be editable

---

## 🧭 Editing Strategy

When making changes:

1. Identify if change is:
   - Style → CSS file
   - Layout → JSON template
   - Component → section/block

2. Modify the smallest possible surface area

3. Preserve:
   - Theme editor compatibility
   - Existing merchant settings

---

## 🧪 Output Expectations

- Always return FULL updated file
- Do NOT return partial snippets unless asked
- Keep formatting Shopify-compatible

---

## 🏷 Context Awareness

This theme includes:

- OPTICA → homepage (luxury, editorial)
- Atelier → reusable components
- Horizon → base system

Respect this separation at all times.
